GlucosePlugin is part of the Utah Decision Support Tools.

Author:
J. Michael Dean, M.D., M.B.A.

Aug 4, 2006 8:15:05 PM

University of Utah School of Medicine, Salt Lake City, Utah

Copyright 2005 - 2006. All rights reserved.

Purpose of the class: Control lifecycle of the plugin.

The plugin contains the list of existing patients and the list of decisionsForPatient that are related to the current selection in the PatientView. It also handles adding listeners who are interested in changes in specific decisionsForPatient, mainly to permit updating GUI elements. Thus, this class controls three different items to which others might listen: the current patient list, the current decision, and a list of decisionsForPatient that are related to a selected patient.

addDecisionFiredListener

public void addDecisionFiredListener(IDecisionListener listener)
Adds object as a listener for specific decision changes that occur when the rules engine fires.

Parameters:
listener - - object to be added as a listener for changes in specific decisions, which occur upon firing of the rules engine. Such objects primarily will update textual descriptions of a specific decision, such as displaying the rules trace, etc.

This is NOT the correct place to add a listener for the list of decisions that are relevant to a specific patient.

Sends notification that the rules engine has fired and altered a decision object. This should be called from anywhere in the application that needs to communicate this change to listeners. This is needed in order for the Drools shadow facts to properly change, but does not display anything.
